==English==
===verb===
1. The act of '''ridiculing''' someone or an organisation, is indicating by means of [[laughter]] or [[irony]] the opinion that the ideas or [[behavior]] of the other are '''[[ridiculous]]''', i.e. far from [[normal]] and sensible, and are therefore rejected.

